\
It\'92s also worth pointing out that an animal will determine for itself whether it should prioritize water or food, depending on if it\'92s hungrier or thirstier at any given point. For sheep specifically, they will always prioritize running away from a wolf if they are in immediate danger. Survival is always more important than eating or drinking!\
\
Cool! By now you may have noticed that some sheep are different colors, and some wolves are larger than others. This is due to the mutation system that is built within EcoSim. Every time an animal is born, it has the chance to mutate. In the case of the purple sheep and the large wolves, they were born with a mutation!\
